B.  Received fresh labeled ""rectal biopsy #2"" is a 0.3 x 0.2 x 0.2 cm tan soft tissue.  All submitted.  Grossed by DANIEL.

C.  Received fresh labeled ""rectal biopsy #3"" is a 0.2 x 0.2 x 0.2 cm tan soft tissue.  All submitted.  Grossed by DANIEL.

D.  Received fresh labeled ""ascending, transverse, descending, and sigmoid colon"" is a total abdominal colectomy specimen consisting of 4.0 cm in length portion of ileum, 65.0 cm in length colon, and a no appendix.  A 5.0 x 5.0 x 1.5 cm ulcerated annular mass is present involving the entire ileocecal valve that grossly invades into the fat located 5.0 cm from the terminal ileum margin.  There is an additional 6.0 x 5.2 x 1.2 cm annular infiltrative mass within the transverse colon that grossly invades into the fat.  Multiple lymph nodes are present within the mesenteric fat.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by LARSON.


